OL,4,CGreensill: Top civil servant 'joined
OL,5,Cfirm before quitting'
OL,6, A top civil servant joined financial
OL,7, firm Greensill Capital as an adviser
OL,8, while still working for the government,
OL,9, a lobbying watchdog has revealed.
OL,11,FBill Crothers's part-time position had
OL,12,Fbeen "agreed" to by the Cabinet Office,
OL,13,Fthe Office of the Advisory Committee on
OL,14,FBusiness Appointments added.
OL,16,FIts chairman Lord Pickles complained of
OL,17,Fa "lack of transparency" over the
OL,18,Fsituation.
OL,20,FBut Mr Crothers said he had been taken
OL,21,Fon by Greensill in a "transparent" way.
